30/11/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The National Assembly of Republika Srpska adopted eight amendments to the entity constitution Friday night (28 November). The changes came into force Saturday after being confirmed by the Chamber of Peoples. According to AFP, the National Assembly passed the constitutional amendments with 65 votes in favour of the bill, two votes against, and six abstentions. Ten out of 83 members of the Assembly did not participate in the session. The constitutional changes transfer all defence functions of the Republika Srpska presidency to the tripartite BiH presidency. The parliaments of the BiH Federation and the state should pass similar amendments in order to complete the plan for setting up a joint military system. (SRNA, BTA, AFP - 29/11/03)
